begin_memory_text: We talked a lot about school. We discussed where she went and her major. We also talked about how it's been for her to have class online and be in her dorm by herself.
middle_memory_text: We discussed her parents who are both lawyers(!) We talked about what it was like growing up for her and how her parents' jobs impacted her. We also talked about our childhoods.
end_memory_text: We discussed UGA football and how much she does not really like it. We spoke about some of her classes and how she is doing with them being online. We also talked about how we got into Prolific and some other sites like it.
rest_of_day_open: I think it will go okay. Work suddenly got busy and I'm still trying to learn everything and everyone. I think it will be alright, and I just have to dive in head first. I am nervous and excited for my side hustles, but I also need to prioritize my day job.
critical_positive: I think when we talked about school, that was great. We both had experiences in colleges that were similar, so it was fun getting to chat with someone who was in roughly the same boat. But it was also cool to hear about online schooling for her. I also liked when we talked about her parents and family.
critical_negative: I probably could've let her talk or ask questions more. I felt like I dominated the conversation at times and I should've not always brought up myself after everything she said. I also think I could have let her finish thoughts before I jumped in and started talking while she probably had more to say.

begin_memory_text: At first we talked about our "jobs" (quotes because I'm a student so I don't have a job). I talked about my psychology major and she talked about her job in IKEA marketing and her past job working for marketing for my university.
middle_memory_text: I think this was around when we talked about our parents? (mostly mine) I learned that her parents are an oral surgery assistant and a trucker, and I talked about my parents being lawyers and how that may have affected my childhood
end_memory_text: At the end of the conversation we talked about ways to make money online, such as this survey, others through Prolific and MTurk, and crowd content.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week involves a lot of math homework. It also involves several hours of online tutoring (I tutor mostly high school math) and online classes. In the evenings on the weekend I will spend time with my friends. We usually play board games in the dorm lobby.
critical_positive: The conversation worked well when we found a topic that one or both of us could find funny and/or relate to each other. For example we laughed about my experiences with lawyer parents and she related that to her childhood experience watching law and order and told a funny anecdote.
critical_negative: The conversation would die out a little when we got onto a topic one of couldn't rely relate to. It also didn't work as well when we tried to interrupt each other with anecdotes or comments. Sometimes we would both start talking at the same time and have to figure out who should speak
